design_brief_for_codex.common_schema_wrapper:
Each widget payload is wrapped at the agent â†’ renderer boundary in a common envelope:
```json
{
  "widget_type": "<one of the 23>",
  "variant": "<template-specific variant id>",
  "payload": <per the template's schema>,
  "ai_adjustments": {
    "emphasis": "<template-defined emphasis slot, optional>",
    "annotations": [<bounded annotation objects, optional>],
    "conditional_fields": {<template-defined flag map, optional>}
  },
  "schema_version": 1
}
```
This envelope itself has a schema at `muno/playbooks/widget-contract/_envelope.schema.json`. All 23 template schemas describe ONLY the `payload` sub-schema; the envelope wraps them.
